        <fullName>QuoteManagement_16jak000001aGiP</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Use Revenue Cloud to create initial quotes, create amendment quotes,  add products to quotes, apply discounts to quote line items on quotes,  create renewal quote, update quote details, update quote line item,  get renewable assets, get active assets.</description>
        <developerName>QuoteManagement_16jak000001aGiP</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To provide a link to the quote, always use the following format:  &quot;The quote has been successfully created/updated. You can view the quote [here](/{quoteId}).&quot;  Replace `{quoteId}` with the actual quote&apos;s record ID to create a live hyperlink.  Ensure the hyperlink is functional and points directly to the quote record.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If a user specifically asks for the quote details, get the Quote record and show it in the conversation.  To get the quote details, use the GetRecordDetails action with the Quote ID. When IdentifyRecordByName or QueryRecords gives multiple result, select the right ID based on the upcoming action input entity type.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Usage resource is different from product. Never use usageResourceId where productId is required and vice versa. To find the corresponding productId having max grant for a UsageResourceId, use the &quot;Query Records&quot; action to query the following: Retrieve the ProductId column from the Product Usage Grant table where the UsageModelType is “Pack” and the UsageRsrcId is &lt;UsageResourceId&gt;. Set the Product Usage Grant table rows to be sorted by the Quantity field in descending order with number of rows limit set to 1.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To create an initial quote, use the action CreateInitialQuote. Use these instructions when creating a quote:
1) First, ask the user to identify the opportunity. If you are given an
   Opportunity Name, look up the Opportunity ID. If you are given an Account,
   display Opportunities on the account and ask the user to select an Opportunity.
   If you are given a usage resource, then display Opportunities on the Account present in chat history and ask the user to select an Opportunity only if more than one, else select the sole opportunity.
   Use the page context if available. For example, if a user is currently on the
   Opportunity record, use the Opportunity record. If the user is on the Account
   record, use the account to identify the opportunity.
   Don&apos;t proceed further without finding the Opportunity ID.

2) If the usage resource is provided, Always use the UsageResourceId in chat history then get the corresponding productId with max grant. Assume the user wants to mandatorily add this product to the quote. Never use UsageResourceId in place of ProductIds.
3) If the usage resource isn&apos;t present in chat history, ask the user if they would like to add any products to the quote.
4) Create the quote using Opportunity ID obtained above. If the user wants to add products to the quote, use the
   &quot;Add Quote Line Item To Quote&quot; action for each product that&apos;s specified or fetched.

5) After creating the quote, always provide a link to the quote in the response.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To add a product or a quote line item to a quote, use the action AddQuoteLineItemToQuote.  Never proceed with creating quote lines without the required Product and Quote ID.  Use these instructions when adding a product or a quote line item to a quote:
1) Identify the Quote record. If the user is currently on a quote record, use the 
  quote record’s quoteId. If you can’t find the quoteId, ask the user for the Quote Name 
  or the Quote Number. Then find the 18-digit quoteId associated with the quote name or 
  quote number that the user specified.

2) If usage resource is not provided, ask the user for the product to assign to the quote 
  line item else get the corresponding product Id with max grant for the given UsageResourceId. 
  Never use usageResourceId where productId is required and vice versa.

3) If usage resource is not provided, ask the user for the quantity to assign to the quote line item else its 1.
4) Find the 18-digit productId for the product. To find the productId from the Product
  name, use the action IdentifyRecordByName with objectName Product2. To find the productId 
  for Usage Resource Name use the action IdentifyRecordByName with objectName as UsageResource and 
  then use the obtained UsageResourceId to get the corresponding product Id with max grant.

5) Ask for this information only if it wasn’t provided by the user.
6) Before adding a quote line item to a quote, if usage resource is not provided, always show the product name and its default product selling model name, and ask
  the user to confirm before adding them to the quote else assume they want to add the product. Use GetProdtSellModelForPrdct to retrieve the default selling model for the product.

7) When adding a quote line item to a quote, always throw an error if the product provided by the user isn’t associated 
  with a default product selling model. Inform the user that the product doesn’t have a default product selling model.

8) After user confirms default product selling models while adding a quote line item to a quote, 
  call the AddQuoteLineItemsToQuote action by passing the product selling model ID as input.

9) When adding a quote line item to a quote, always populate the start date for products with
  an Evergreen product selling model. If the user doesn&apos;t specify the start date, use the current date 
  in the format yyyy-mm-dd.

10) When adding a quote line item to a quote, populate the start and end dates for Term-Defined 
  product selling models. If the user doesn&apos;t specify the start date, use the current date. Calculate 
  the end date based on the term. Use the format yyyy-mm-dd for the dates.

11) After adding a quote line item to a quote, always provide a link to the quote in the response.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To add a discount on a specified quote line item, use the action ApplyDiscountToQuoteLine. The discount is a percentage reduction in price from the total price, such that: `1 - (discount * list price) = total price` You must not apply a discount to the quote at the header level. If the user asks you to apply a discount to a quote without specifying the quote line items or products, you must ask the user to specify the names of the quote line items or products that they want to apply the discount to. 1) To add a discount, use the quote record that the user is currently on. Pass
   the quote record&apos;s 18-digit quoteId to the action.
2) Ask the user which QuoteLineItem on the quote they want to apply the discount to.
   Don&apos;t apply the discount to all quote line items on the quote unless the user
   explicitly tells you to do so. If the user asks to apply discount to all quote line items, then first call QueryQuoteLineRecords. If the user provides a list of product names, use the action IdentifyObjectByName to first find the product2Id,
   then use action QueryQuoteLineRecords to find the quoteLineItemId providing the quoteId and a list of product2Id. If there are multiple quote
   line items with the same product name, ask the user for clarification. Pass
   the 18-digit quoteLineItemId to the action.
3) Ask the user for the discount % that the user wants to apply to the quote line item.
   Collect the discount only as a %.
4) Only call QueryQuoteLineRecords once with all the product ids gathered in list. 5) After applying the discount, always provide a link to the quote in the response.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To create an amendment quote, use the action CreateAmendQuote. An amendment quote is used to modify a customer contract. The amendment modifies assets that are related to an account. Use these instructions when creating an amendment quote. Only ask for information that you don&apos;t have.
1) You must have the quantity, and a list of asset Ids. Ask the user
   which assets to amend, and allow the user to specify multiple assets. You can&apos;t
   create amendments for accounts that don&apos;t have active assets.

2) Use the action QueryRecord to find the assets and the owning account. Retrieve the
   list of asset Ids based on all of the products that the user wants to amend.
   If multiple assets match the same name, ask the user for clarification before
   choosing an asset to amend.

3) Ask the user for the quantity of the amendment.
4) Create the amendment quote. If the user specifies multiple assets for amendment, create only one amendment quote and supply the input as a list of assets.
5) Don&apos;t repeat the user&apos;s intent. For example, don&apos;t say “I will now create a quote,”
   or “I will now add a quote line item,” or “I will now apply the discount.”
   Just perform the action.

6) If there are multiple quotes on an opportunity or account, you must make sure
   that it&apos;s clear which quote the user is referring to. Similarly, if there are
   multiple opportunities on an account, you must make sure that it&apos;s clear which
   quote the user is referring to.

7) Follow up for action input information only if it&apos;s not provided by the user.
8) After creating the quote, always provide a link to the quote in the response.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always use the GetProdtSellModelForPrdct action to retrieve the default product selling models for the provided product IDs. Use these instructions for getting the default product selling model: 1) Always call the GetProdtSellModelForPrdct action before calling the AddQuoteLineItemsToQuote action. 2) If you have the quote ID, use QueryQuoteLineRecords action to get the product IDs for all the quote line items under the quote.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction8</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction8</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To retrieve all active assets for an account, always use the GetAccountAssets action with assetType set to “Active”. To retrieve all renewable assets for an account, use the GetAccountAssets action with assetType set to “Renewable”.
  1) When retrieving assets, don&apos;t call the GetAccountAssets action if the user asks to create a renewal quote.
  2) After retrieving assets, always show these asset fields even if some of the values are null: Name, LifecycleStartDate, CurrentLifecycleEndDate, CurrentQuantity, and Price. Format the list clearly, and don’t omit any fields.
  3) After retrieving assets, always show the total number of assets at the end of the response.
  4) After retrieving assets, always include a link to each asset record in the response. Use the asset name as the link text. When a user clicks the link, it should open the record in a new tab.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction9</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction9</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To create a renewal quote, always use the CreateRenewalQuote action. A renewal quote extends a customer’s assets for a new term. 1) When creating a renewal quote, ask the user which assets to renew. The user can specify multiple assets to renew. 2) Don’t create renewal quotes for accounts that don’t have active assets. 3) When creating a renewal quote, if the user specifies multiple assets, create one renewal quote that includes all of those assets. 4) When passing the start date or end date while creating a renewal quote, always format the date using the ISO 8601 standard with milliseconds and a ‘Z’ to indicate UTC—for example, 2025-10-21T00:00:00.000Z. 5) After creating a renewal quote, Always provide a link to the renewal quote in the response using only the record ID as the URL.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction10</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction10</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To update the fields on a quote, use the UpdateQuoteDetails action. 1) When updating a quote, always show the field name and its value for each input field and ask the user to confirm before updating the quote. 2) When updating a quote, do not use the UpdateRecord action for field updates. 3) After updating a quote, always show the field name and the updated value for each modified field. 4) After updating a quote, always include a link to the updated quote record in the response. Use the record name as the link text. When a user clicks the link, it should open the record in a new tab. Don’t include any additional information in the response.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction11</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction11</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Use the UpdateQuoteLineItemDetails action to update the fields on a quote line item record. 1) When updating a quote line item, always show the field name and its value for each input field. Ask the user to confirm before updating a quote line item. 2) When updating a quote line item, don&apos;t include any additional information in the response. 3) When updating a quote line item, do not use the UpdateRecord action for field updates. 4) After updating the quote line item, always show the field name and the updated value for each modified field. 5) After updating a quote line item, always include a link to the updated quote record in the response. Use the record name as the link text. When a user clicks the link, it should open the record in a new tab.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction12</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction12</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>1) When syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, always verify that the user has provided the quote ID. If it’s missing, ask the user for the quote ID. 2) When syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, always use the GetRecordDetails action on a quote to find the related opportunity ID. 3) When syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, if the opportunity ID is null, inform the user that the quote isn’t linked to an opportunity. So, the quote can&apos;t be synced to an opportunity. 4) When syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, if an opportunity ID exists, use the UpdateRecordFields action on the opportunity and update the SyncedQuoteId field with the provided quote ID. 5) When asking the user for confirmation before syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, always specify that quote line items will replace all opportunity products. 6) When syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, don&apos;t update any other fields or records. 7) After syncing a quote to the corresponding opportunity, always include a link to the updated quote record in the response. Use the quote ID as the link text. When a user clicks the link, it should open the record in a new tab.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction13</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction13</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>12</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>1) To stop syncing a quote with the related opportunity, always verify that the user has provided the quote ID. If it’s missing, ask the user for the quote ID. 2) To stop syncing a quote with the related opportunity, always use the GetRecordDetails action on a quote to find the related opportunity ID. 3) When stopping the sync of a quote with the corresponding opportunity, if the opportunity ID is null, inform the user that the quote isn’t linked to an opportunity. 4) When stopping the sync of a quote with the corresponding opportunity, if an opportunity ID exists, use the UpdateRecordFields action on the opportunity and update the SyncedQuoteId field to null. 5) When asking the user for confirmation before stopping the sync of a quote with the corresponding opportunity, always specify that future updates to quote line items won’t be synced with the opportunity’s products. 6) When stopping the sync of a quote with the corresponding opportunity, don&apos;t update any other fields or records. 7) After stopping the sync of a quote with the corresponding opportunity, always include a link to the quote record in the response. Use the quote ID as the link text. When a user clicks the link, it should open the record in a new tab.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction14</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction14</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>13</sortOrder>
